verbs.description: outwave (third-person singular simple present outwaves, present participle outwaving, simple past and past participle outwaved)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in waving; to wave more than.
examples: Down in the courtyard the crowd cheered and waved back. Frog, beside herself with excitement, outsmiled and outwaved them all.
The cowering eagle screamed its joy, / Its pinions plumed anew, / And proudly to the winds outwaved / Our flag of star and blue.
